Components i used to in creating the application    
Components
ScrollView
The ScrollView component is used to create a scrollable container for the app's content.
It allows users to scroll through the content vertically or horizontally, depending on the layout requirements.
Text
The Text component is used to display text content in the app
It supports various text styles, such as font family, size, weight, and color.
View
The View component is a fundamental building block for creating layouts and containers in React Native.
It acts as a container for other components and can be styled with various properties like background color, padding, and margin.
TextInput
The TextInput component is used to create input fields where users can enter text.
It supports various properties like placeholder text, keyboard type, and input validation.
Image
The Image component is used to display images in the app.
It can load images from local files or remote URLs.
TouchableOpacity
The TouchableOpacity component is used to create tappable elements in the app.
It provides visual feedback when the user interacts with the component, making it suitable for buttons or other interactive elements.
StatusBar
The StatusBar component is used to manage the appearance and behavior of the device's status bar.
It allows you to control properties like background color, text color, and visibility.


